post_text: Thank you First Central State Bank!
shared_text:
First Central State Bank
August 18 at 7:05 PM ·

We recently came together to donate $1,000 to the Clinton Community School District toward PPE costs for the 2020-21 school year.

We've long been a supporter of our area schools. With the uncertainty surrounding those schools for the school year, we wanted to help them prepare for a year unlike any other.

That's why we're donating money to our area schools to purchase additional items, such as PPE, so they're safer when opening this fall. Overall, First Central State Bank is committing $5,000 to area schools this fall.

#CommunityBanking

https://www.firstcentralsb.bank/community

Given the circumstances currently in the city of Clinton and the school district due to Monday’s storm damage, along with conversations with Alliant Energy, the district will not be ready for teacher in-service tomorrow. Therefore the first day for teachers will be Monday, August 17 and students will be Thursday, August 20.

Thanks for your understanding.

shared_text:
Clinton High School
July 22 at 9:21 AM ·

The CHS Athletic Boosters and the CHS Athletic Department would like to thank all the local Corporate Members for their support and contributions. Clinton High School students are directly impacted by all moneys donated to the club. Funds are used to purchase team uniforms and equipment, as well as facility upkeep and improvements.

If your business or corporation would like to become a corporate member, contact Activities Director at 563-243-7540 ext. 1182. If you are unable to print this form, please message us your email address and we will email you the PDF form.

Thanks and Go Kings and Queens!

post_text:
Each year, Community Action of Eastern Iowa works to get school supplies to children of low-income families. This year, because of COVID-19, instead of backpacks Community Action of Eastern Iowa is giving out $25 gift cards to Wal-Mart for each child in the family if they qualify based on income. Families can apply online https://www.caeiowa.org/school

Individuals or businesses interested in donating can also visit the CAE website for more information.

Please share this so the families in Clinton and surrounding communities have the information. Thank you!

post_text:
Tomorrow can’t come soon enough for these guys!!!

Come on out to Special Olympics Night in Yourd Gymnasium! This is a free event for all athletes, students, staff, and families! We will start off by showcasing our skills with the assistance of Leo’s Club at 5:30! Then we will move into a five on five game, a three on three game and finish the night w another five on five game! Our Special Olympic athletes will play basketball with the CHS JV/Varsity boys and girls!!! The cheerleaders will lead everyone in the stands with chants and cheers to involve the crowd! Let’s Bring on our CHS school spirit by packing the gym! There will be a bake sale and donation jar to help raise money for summer games!!! Also, we will have applications For anybody interested in becoming a peer buddy during competitions and summer games!
Coaches MB Kokjohn and Terry Kenney

post_text: The Clinton High School Vocal Music Department is once again offering Singing Valentines to the community. Singing Valentine delivery will be from 8am until 2:30 pm on February 14, 2020 to any address within the city limits of Clinton. Featured singers this year will be the members of the CHS Women’s Triple Trio. The women look forward to delivering Singing valentines to both men and women this year. Each recipient will be serenaded and then presented with a small Valentines Day Gift. The cost of each Singing Valentine is $20. Orders may be placed by calling 243-7540 ext. 2061 between 8:00am and 4:00pm on Friday, January 31, 2020 through Monday, February 10, 2020. The Department cannot promise to deliver Singing Valentines at any specific times however persons may specify whether they would like their Valentine delivered between 8:00am and 12:15 pm or from 12:30pm until 3:00 pm. All proceeds will benefit the Clinton High School Choral Music Department.

Be sure to tweet #WPMOYChallenge Johnson to help him earn a $25,000 contribution to the charity of his choice. Make sure to leave a space between the hashtag and Johnson!

Arizona Cardinals
December 12, 2019 at 10:25 AM ·

David Johnson has been named our 2019 #WPMOY nominee for his incredible work in the community.

Be sure to tweet #WPMOYChallenge + David Johnson to help him earn a $25,000 contribution to the charity of his choice.

Congratulations, David! 👏

post_text: Like good food?! Well we want to feed you! Looking for community members to come dine with us this Friday, 11:45-12:45 in the Court Cafe! On the menu is Broccoli Cheese soup, Winter Salad, Garlic Butter Bake Pork Chip and finishing with a Raspberry-Lemon Cake. Please contact Mrs. Toppert at ltoppert@clintonia.org!

post_text: GET YOUR TICKETS!!! The Quad City Storm Hockey team is going to have a “CCSD Night” on March 7. It is also their Marvel Superheroes First Responders game and the Clinton Fire Department will be honored that night as well. CHS choir is going to perform the National Anthem and our band is going to be the pep band of the night.

Clinton Community School District
November 20, 2019 at 2:25 PM ·

Here is a breakdown of the Thanksgiving days off for the different grade levels:

Elementary and Middle School off November 27, 28, 29 and December 2nd. Elementary and Middle School will be back in session on December 3rd.

High School off November 27, 28, and 29th. High School will be back in session on December 2nd.

post_text: CHS staff and students participated in a door decorating contest over the past few weeks! Wellness teacher Mrs. Cewe took home first place with her kids! Also, staff participated in a Chili Cook-Off, with Counselor Mrs. Schrader taking home top honors! Way to go! Huge thank you to Mrs. Slocum for the awesome ideas for each! Huge success!
